<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kibagami Suggilate</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-23 11:41:14</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>this is a post in answer to LF....dont go with all monks, and dont go if your group is all monks under 30...at 35, EVERYTHING on the 1st floor aggroes.  take a well rounded party, i suggest 1 cleric, 1 shammy (for those kick ass buffs), 2 monks (to split the cresent since its no drop) and a druid or ranger, try for a ranger since u alrdy have 2 healers in the group.  i say a druid cuz he can SNARE (kly like to run) and EVAC in case of emergancy.  No one in your group should be under lvl 33 if your going to go to the 2nd lvl.  head for Freeport before u go and buy some inv potions to get out incase u fall to the 3rd floor. me and some other from my group fell in there VERY hard to get our without INV.  1 of the tanks needs to be around lvl 37 or 38, that way u can pull to the pool room and not have to worry about trains when pulling from Lumpy Goo's caves.  GOOD LUCK!! I HOPE I HELPED U SOME!!<BR>
<BR>
Kibagami Suggilate, 1st officer of the Crimson Horde Elders, Bertoxxilous Server</font></td></tr></table>
