<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Scoopmeister</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-03 15:11:36</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>This is all you need to know to get Crescent Armor:<BR>
<BR>
...Learn the layout of Dalnir's.<BR>
<BR>
Lear how to get to the second floor.  Learn how to get off the second floor.  Learn how to get to the third floor.  Learn where the sarcophagus room, smith room, crusader room, chapel, and Overseer are.  Learn how to get off the third floor (it's tricky).  How do you do this?  Buy a bunch of invis potions and keep them on you.  Get an Invis from a caster whenever you can.  Then explore the area.<BR>
<BR>
Once you know the area, you will find that tons of people fight at the zone, a few on the second floor, and fewer on the third floor.  Overall, it doesn't matter.  Find a group and shout to the zone "Would like to loot unused Crescent please".  If you are lucky, and there are only a few Monks in the zone, you may get a tell with the location of a Kly corpse with Crescent on it.  Get an Invis (make sure you have at least 1 Invis potion on you) and go loot the armor.  Since it removes invis, use your potion to reinvis and head to the portal.<BR>
<BR>
My level 28 monk never once joined a group to get Crescent.  I would simply run through Dalnir's to groups who were camping the second or third floor and ask if I could hang out for Crescent.  At the same time I would practice my 1HB and 2HB skills.<BR>
<BR>
Of course, you can get Crescent by working your way through Dalnirs with a good group, but do NOT let Crescent rot when all you have to do is learn the dungeon.<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kablooey</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-25 23:29:05</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I'm a 45 druid camping the crusader and the occasional lumpy and kly imprecator or kly yard trash for the past three days SOLID--huge hours.<BR>
<BR>
I'd suggest that if anyone goes, they take a druid.  Not only is an extra healer always welcome, and a snare, and a SOW once you zone out of the dungeon, but also because all the "coerced" that the dungeon is full of count as summoned except for coerced iksars and coerced goblins.  Druids have the strongest anti-summoned spells in the game, as they get a bonus in that area just like clerics get bonuses against undead.  Granted this dungeon was below my level, but it was still nice to see how easy my anti-summoned spells took out the coerced compared to my regular blasts.<BR>
<BR>
Another thing that should be repeated is that everything aggros here, so a druid is also good to keep everyone on superior camouflage (regular doesn't work indoors).  Other casters can do this as well, too, of course.  But getting to the second floor, where the really good drops begin, means getting through quite a few mobs, and when everyone's beat up and crying, an invis is very welcome so that people can catch their breath and med or heal.  Bring at least SOMEONE who can invis all the time.  And try to invis before you even zone in, because spawns wander right by the entrance.<BR>
<BR>
The only other thing I can think of adding at this moment is the kly casters seem to aggro on me a lot more, even at level 45, than the melee do.  The Kly is blue to me, and so is a Kly Invoker once in a rare while.  Everything else is green.  But green Kly casters still aggro on me sometime.  Other mobs like goos and ravenous nibblers aggro about 50% of the time, for my level or lower--probably all levels.</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
